capable teams would have a chance to beat them?  Hell no, so why would you ask me to do the same?  Ok this is the bad guy side of me, I'll explain the good guy side now hehe.<br><br>Will I share something with you?  Of course I will if you ask in a respectful and polite manner within reason.  See the problem I have is with people that DEMAND things of you when they should be asking.  <br><br>Bad - &quot;You will not have the next spawn because you had the last two&quot;<br><br>Good - &quot;Do you think you we could get the next spawn of this mob?<br><br>Bad - &quot;WTF do you mean I can't come on this Trakanon raid?  You don't own this mob and I need a damn BP, you guys are just farming!&quot;<br><br>Good - &quot;I'd love to come on a raid sometime and hangout with you guys if you have any room for me&quot;<br><br>The Bad dialogues invoke the bad guy side of me and the good dialogues invoke the carebear side of me.  I don't have any inherent disrespect for anyone.  I don't have a superiority complex where I think I'm naturally better then other people.   So.... that's me though I'm sure I'm missing parts.<br><br>Now onto this Uber Mentality.  This is the mentality that most Uber Guilds seem to have and yes I will be stereotyping here and this certainly won't cover every guild out there.  <br><br>-Every uber guild is made up of power gamers with very few exceptions.  Uber guilds are about doing the hardest feats, fighting the hardest mobs, and getting the best loots.  Power gamers naturally migrate to uber guilds.  Uber guilds are about being the best with the best in order to get the best.<br><br>-Uber guilds are capitalists.  Most believe in FCFS, don't whine.  A FFAish type atmosphere favors Uber guilds because of their effiency.  <br><br>-Generally speaking uber guilds don't get along with eachother.  Imagine two highly competitive entities constantly competing with eachother for spawns over a prolonged period of time then you throw in the occasional cock waving for shits and giggles.  <br><br>-Uber guilds don't like whiners.  Hmmm how can I say this... if Uber guild SuK is beaten to a spawn by Uber guild WeRule some possible responses are: Flame about it on a message board, Demand that the uber guild share and GIVE them the spawn since it takes them more effort to raid, bitch and moan that now they have nothing to do.  Now I'm NOT saying this is what all uber guilds do, I'm just giving some examples of guilds with a BAD mentality.  On the flip side if Uber guild SuK beats Uber guild WeRule to a spawn, WeRule goes to find something else to kill and doesn't complain or bitch up a storm about it.  <br><br>-Uber guilds tend to have very loyal guild members.  If an Uber Guild completely broke up its likely that many members would quit since the only reason why they played was for the guild.  Conquest is a good example.<br><br>Well I'm getting kind of sleepy if I think of more I'll add it.  This is MY opinion only, not fact, gospel, or any organization's opinion.  Just throwing around some debate material here.  I'm sure some people hate uber guilds and feel that they take away some of their gaming experience, others have different opinions on what an uber guild is so lets hear them.  If you want to flame go ahead :P  I won't get involved in any personal flaming but I'd be happy to debate some <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br> <p>----------------------- <BR>Zartuul the Tactician <BR>Grave Lord, Zeb <BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uzartuulthetactician.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zartuul the Tactician</A> at: 8/8/01 9:51:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/unaathankaine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naathan Kaine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered